This paper deals with the safety verification of deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and security and privacy (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel automated verification framework, which involves the use of Satisfiability Modulo Theory (SMT), a topic that falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CR, and cs.SY, in that order.
